records.addlTxt:
01:43 PM Defendant Eduardo Serna in court, in custody, with attorney Jessica A Klein.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Niki Kane, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for sentencing after a plea was entered 6/09/22.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the court.

Court orders the following:
IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:

TOTAL PRISON:  3 YEARS;
INITIAL CONFINEMENT:  1.5 YEARS;
EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1.5 YEARS;
IF REVOKED:
0   Days Credit.
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

TERM OF PROBATION:   2  Years, Court does not object to transfer to Milwaukee or Sheboygan County; 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores);
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel in Waukesha County;
*Do not drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid license; Comply with all drivers licensing restrictions; 
*DNA sample to be provided;

CONDITION TIME:
90  DAYS in the Waukesha County Jail - 1st 45 DAYS as Straight-time, following 45 DAYS may be served with Huber (with standard release conditions) or electronic monitoring if the Sheriff deems it appropriate.
2 DAYS Credit.

D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

FINE: $3,089, includes IID surcharge; 
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $24 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to City of Brookfield Police Department. 
Payment of all Fees/Fines/Surcharges are a condition of probation and are to be converted to civil judgment for non-payment.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
